Former Fulham midfielder Pajtim Kasami scored the only goal as Olympiacos shocked Juventus with a 1-0 victory in the Champions League on Wednesday night. 

The Swiss international struck in the 36th minute in Piraeus to hand his team three valuable points in Group A.

The victory leaves the Greek champions level on points with Atletico Madrid, who sit second after hammering Malmo 5-0 at the Vicente Calderon. 

